The paper discusses a toolkit for algorithm selection and portfolio techniques, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The toolkit leverages machine learning algorithms and techniques in R, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the modular and extensible nature of the toolkit, which is a common feature in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
